snippet.textDisplay:
There weren't too many snack options at my grandma's house so I used to just straight up eat white sugar as a kid. I also ate so much chocolate and candy. I drank so much soda during parties. I had a sweet tooth and there weren't enough healthy snacks around most of the time (except for fruit).

Now that I'm 23, I can't process sugar too well anymore and I get a little sick if I eat dessert that's a little too sweet. I also have to water down my soda a bit now.

Edit: just to clarify, I didn't just eat sweets as a kid. I liked fruit and veggies as well.
